\pard\plain \fi720\ltrch\loch {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Good and Evil are some of the most real and powerful forces that we interact with on a daily basis. As with the force of Love, Good and Evil are actions and therefore can only be described in the active tense. That is to say, to be good or evil to another is to help or to harm it. Things such as clean water that are considered ultimately good are really only good to the majority of others around. Serial killers are considered only because they act with more evil than good. When analyzed in this way, the morality of Good and Evil breaks down into the utilitarianism of help versus harm.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Some would think that help is difficult to define, but it\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 s easy so long as you have a simple definition of harm: \hich\f0 \ldblquote \loch\f0 to damage or otherwise limit the full-spectrum well-being of something.\hich\f0 \rdblquote \loch\f0  Help can be thought of simply as health and wellness, but on a deeper level every human being (and many animals) seem to require:}
